(Ford GoBike System)¶

by (Adham AlQattawy)¶

Preliminary Wrangling¶

The data set is called Fordgobike, This data set includes information about individual rides made in a bike-sharing system covering the greater San Francisco Bay area, and represents trips taken by members of the service for month of February of 2019

The Features:

  • duration_sec: duration per second
  • start_time: the time that the trip started at
  • end_time: the time that the trip ended at
  • start_station_id
  • start_station_name
  • start_station_latitude
  • start_station_longitude
  • end_station_id
  • end_station_name
  • end_station_latitude
  • end_station_longitude
  • bike_id
  • user_type
  • member_birth_year
  • member_gender
  • bike_share_for_all_trip

What is the structure of your dataset?¶

This data set includes information about individual rides made in a bike-sharing system covering the greater San Francisco Bay area.It includes 183412 rows and 16 feature (duration_sec, start_time, end_time, start_station_id, start_station_name, start_station_latitude, start_station_longitude, end_station_id, end_station_name, end_station_latitude, end_station_longitude, bike_id, user_type, member_birth_year, member_gender, bike_share_for_all_trip). There are 9 numeric features and 7 categorical features.**

What is/are the main feature(s) of interest in your dataset?¶

After looking at the data, the main features of interest are (start_time, end_time, start_station_name, end_station_name, user_type, member_birth_year)

What features in the dataset do you think will help support your investigation into your feature(s) of interest?¶

The feature that will help me with my investigation are (duration_sec, member_gender)

Discuss the distribution(s) of your variable(s) of interest. Were there any unusual points? Did you need to perform any transformations?¶

  • The common ages of riders are from 25 to 40 years.
  • There are more males riders that females riders.
  • The number of subscribers were more bigger than the customers number.
  • the number of trips were at 8am and 5pm.
  • The number of trips on saturday and sunday were less than the rest of the week.
  • the most station the has users is Market st at 10th st

Of the features you investigated, were there any unusual distributions? Did you perform any operations on the data to tidy, adjust, or change the form of the data? If so, why did you do this?¶

  • First I got the Age distribution and there were an outliers so I changed the range to be from 0 to 80 so that the distribution be more clear.
  • The duration by seconds were not clear, so that I changed the range to be from 0 to 2500 so that the distribution be more clear
